
[1]purposely

   PUR'POSELY, adv. By design; intentionally; with predetermination.

   In composing this discourse, I purposely declined all offensive and
   displeasing truths.

   So much they scorn the crown, I purposely declined all offensive and
   displeasing truths.

   So much they scorn the crown, that if the throng

   By chance go right, they purposely go wrong.
